about.description:
ipyxact is a helper library that creates python structures from parsed
IP-Xact files. It is intended to make it easier to use IP-Xact files in a
python application

name: ipyxact
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "ipyxact" %}
{% set version = "0.2.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ebc8877ed5ace838a006ab299b5cf533d3e91d388f8d7e3ace96b1232d7fbba2

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - pyyaml

test:
  imports:
    - ipyxact

about:
  home: https://github.com/olofk/ipyxact
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Python-based IP-XACT parser'
  description: |
    ipyxact is a helper library that creates python structures from parsed
    IP-Xact files. It is intended to make it easier to use IP-Xact files in a
    python application

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - hmaarrfk
